### 6. Module 4: `src/modules/sketch/editor/inferenceCache.js` -- Memoized Point Collection

Computing inference points for all parts on every mouse move is wasteful. This module provides a simple cache that recomputes only when the parts array reference changes.

```javascript
export function createInferenceCache() {
  let cachedParts = null;
  let cachedPoints = null;

  return {
    getPoints(parts, excludePartId = null) {
      if (parts !== cachedParts) {
        cachedParts = parts;
        cachedPoints = collectInferencePoints(parts);
      }
      if (excludePartId) {
        return cachedPoints.filter(p => p.partId !== excludePartId);
      }
      return cachedPoints;
    },
    invalidate() {
      cachedParts = null;
      cachedPoints = null;
    },
  };
}
```

This cache lives in `SketchViewport.jsx` as a ref (`useRef(createInferenceCache())`). It is passed into handlers as part of the context object. The cache is automatically invalidated when `visibleParts` changes (since `parts !== cachedParts` will be true with a new array reference from the React state update).

**Scaling analysis:** A typical furniture project has 10-50 parts. Each part produces 8 corners + 12 midpoints + 6 face centers = 26 inference points. For 50 parts = 1300 points. The nearest-neighbor search is O(n) per mouse move, which is ~1300 distance computations -- completely negligible. No spatial index is needed.

